subject: Re: Example Sentence
msgSnippet: Here s an attempt based upon the quick animal series and some of the other posts thus far in this thread: The quick beige whippoorwills are jumping, flying
messageBody:
Here's an attempt based upon "the quick animal" series and some of the
other posts thus far in this thread:

"The quick beige whippoorwills are jumping, flying and hopping in the
air just over each and every thin, crazy sheepdog."

I score this one 36/40 for the main alphabet and 41/47 including the
ligatures. (Do you folks think this is a valid way to score these
sentences?)

Mind you, I am from the Atlanta, Georgia area, so I am tempted to
say/write "dog" with the typical southern drawl (although I didn't
this time for the purposes of keeping the exercise more universal).

-CJ
